modules.description: Provides hash table operations for key-value storage and retrieval, including insertion, deletion, and lookup. Works with string-based keys and values, supporting persistent storage through file-backed databases. Used to manage session data in web applications and cache frequently accessed information.

The module provides operations for handling key-value databases, including reading, writing, updating, and iterating over entries using database handles and cursor objects. It supports transaction management and cursor-based traversal, particularly for sorted data, enabling efficient data manipulation and consistent state management. Use cases include scenarios requiring synchronized access, sorted data navigation, and high-performance key-value operations.
